  • Delete the ânameâ, âteam_idâ, and âfg3_pctâ variables.

    bball = bball %>% select(-team_id, - fg3_pct)
    bball = bball %>% select(-name)

  • Convert the âposâ variable to a factor (this variable represents the playerâs position).

    bball = bball %>% mutate(pos = as_factor(pos))

  • Filter out (remove) all players with âmp_per_gâ values less 25.

    bball = bball %>% filter(mp_per_g < 25)

  • Perform row-wise deletion of missingness.

    bball = drop_na(bball)

  • There are some odd hybrid positions in the âposâ variable (this variable captures player positions). These hybrid positions all have the â-â character in them. Use the code provided below to filter them out (as part of your data-cleaning code):

    bball = bball %>% filter(!str_detect(pos, "-")) %>% droplevels()

filter(!str_detect(pos, â-â)) %>% droplevels()

Q3 USING THE TIDYMODEL FRAMEWORK, create a linear regression model with the âpts_per_gâ variable to predict âbpmâ. Comment on the linear regression model results. Is this a good model?

bball_recipe = recipe(bpm ~ pts_per_g, data = bball)

lm_model = linear_reg() %>% set_engine("lm")

lm_wflow = workflow() %>% add_model(lm_model) %>% add_recipe(bball_recipe)
lm_fit = fit(lm_wflow, bball)
lm_fit
